<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12053o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12053o">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12053o"> 53(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> kinderwallfahrt</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">55-6: Nous trouverons dans les chroniques allemandes d&apos;utiles et curieux renseignements sur ces p&egrave;lerinages enfantins. / Trithemius nous rapporte qu&apos;&agrave; la date de 1456 des milliers d&apos;enfants vinrent au sanctuaire du &laquo;Saint Archange Michel au Mont Garganus en Normandie (sic). &laquo;On ignore, continue-t-il, ce qui les faisait entreprendre un si long voyage, sans que personne les invit&acirc;t, sans &ecirc;tre attir&eacute;s par des promesses quelconques; ils y allaient sans prendre l&apos;avis de leurs parents sans ressources, sans argent, ne voulant m&ecirc;me subvenir aux besoins de leur voyage qu&apos;au moyen d&apos;aum&ocirc;nes recueillies en cours de route. C&apos;&eacute;taient, pour la plupart, des enfants de 12 ans. Ils chantaient des cantiques &agrave; saint Michel et &eacute;taient pr&eacute;c&eacute;d&eacute;s d&apos;un drapeau portant l&apos;image de l&apos;archange. Je les ai vus bien souvent passer en troupes.&raquo; <br>[In the German chronicles we find useful and curious information about these <mark>children&apos;s pilgrimages</mark>. Trithemus tells us that in 1456 thousands of children came to the Sanctuary of &ldquo;the Holy Archangel Michael of Mont Garganus in Normandy (sic). We don&apos;t know, he continues, why they made such a long trip, without being invited by anybody, without having been attracted by any promises; they went without advice of their parents, without resources, without money, insisting on paying the travel costs by means of alms collected on the way. For the most part these were children of 13 years old. They sang canticles to Saint Michael and before them went a flag with an image of the archangel. I have often seen them pass in groups. <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 55-6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: German <i>Kinderwallfahrt</i>: children&apos;s pilgrimage. </mm> </dd></dl>
